<br>
This day we hae received assurance that a proper majik foundation hast been prepared for it in the form of a formal hosting at a friendly site. Here in the Dire Plane of Reality where I sit we have called upon a great mage of the majiks of FTP und HTML und Java tae call our dear hime from the nether regions where it drifts as a ghost. Offer whatever sacrifice is called for by yer gods that we may see it firmly grounded and again open fer aer feet soon. <p>For Halas! For MacLear!<BR>
Spectamur Agendo!<BR>
<BR>
Tormod MacLear, Chief</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/utormodmaclear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tormod MacLear</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chief</span><br>  Posts: 428<br> <font color=#330000>(7/30/01 12:09:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1129.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.clanmaclear.com/images/tormod.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Castle MacLear</span><hr size=1> I know this is a reply to my first post, but what th' heck, I'm used to talkin' to meself. <br>
<br>
OOC: At the new hosting site we have the ability to use a built in messageboard (amazing what one can get from hosting a few URLs and paying each month). The messageboard we are considering would be a bit more formal than we previously have seen. In order to enter one would have to have an approved username and be granted a unique password. As some of you are aware, the current messageboard is open to literally anyone who can find it. While we have had only small amount of trouble in the past with this issue, it is one that I believe needs addressing.<br>
<br>
Additionally, we propose to make the site the home for ALL MacLears from any and every game we are now in or will be in for the future. <br>
<br>
Last but not least, we are considering using the site services to eventually provide us with a dedicated server to host games that are not yet in existance, but are anticipated. The guaranteed bandwith we would be purchasing would be measured in gigabits. The possibility exists that we might ask a monthly fee of $5 or so if and when that happens for those who want to use the server. None of this is even vaguely solid, but just some thinking about the capabilities we have gained in the move.<br>
<br>
Those amongst ye with an opinion on these issues are welcome to comment. <p>For Halas! For MacLear!<BR>
Spectamur Agendo!<BR>
<BR>
Tormod MacLear, Chief</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nakor>Nakor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#330000>(7/30/01 3:34:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1129.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Castle MacLear</span><hr size=1> Tormod,<br>
